          <p style="color:#94A3B8;font-size:13px;">Last updated: July 2026 · Framed with reference to India's Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act, 2023</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">BMD Calculator (no account needed)</h2>
          <p>The Bone Mineral Density calculator is free and anonymous — no account or login is required. We store the measurements you enter and the resulting score so you can revisit your printable report. If you choose to enter an email address (entirely optional), we use it only to send you that result — we do not use it for marketing without your separate consent.</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">What we collect</h2>
          <p>When you create an account and use the Menopause Forecast, we collect:</p>
          <ul style="line-height:1.9;">
            <li><strong>Account data</strong> — your email address, name, and a securely hashed password (we never store your password itself).</li>
            <li><strong>Profile data</strong> — the display name, relationship label, and optional date of birth of each health profile you create (up to 3 per account).</li>
            <li><strong>Health test inputs</strong> — age, AMH blood value, and menstrual cycle regularity that you enter for a forecast.</li>
            <li><strong>Payment records</strong> — order status and payment reference IDs from our payment gateway (Razorpay). Your card/UPI details are handled entirely by the gateway and never touch our servers.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">Why we collect it</h2>
          <p>We use this data for exactly one purpose: computing and storing your menopause forecast so you can access it whenever you want. We do not sell your data, share it with advertisers, or use it for any purpose you have not consented to.</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">Your consent</h2>
          <p>At signup you give explicit, un-preticked consent to this processing, as required by the DPDP Act. You may withdraw consent at any time by requesting deletion of your account (below) — withdrawal does not affect the lawfulness of processing done before withdrawal.</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">How long we keep it</h2>
          <p>Your account, profiles, and paid results are kept for as long as your account exists, so that results you have paid for remain permanently accessible to you. Payment records are retained as required for accounting and tax purposes.</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">Your rights</h2>
          <ul style="line-height:1.9;">
            <li><strong>Access</strong> — you can view all your profiles, results, and orders from your dashboard at any time.</li>
            <li><strong>Correction</strong> — contact us to correct inaccurate account details.</li>
            <li><strong>Erasure</strong> — request deletion of your account and all associated data by writing to us from your registered email via the <a href="/contact.asp">contact page</a>. We will confirm deletion within 7 working days.</li>
            <li><strong>Grievance</strong> — if you believe your data has been mishandled, contact us first; you also have the right to complain to the Data Protection Board of India.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">Security</h2>
          <p>Passwords are stored using bcrypt hashing, all payment confirmation is verified server-side with cryptographic signatures, and access to stored health data is restricted to your authenticated account.</p>

          <h2 class="aboutpage-title">Contact</h2>
          <p>For any privacy question or request, reach us through the <a href="/contact.asp">contact page</a> or at hello@e-healthwatch.com.</p>

